      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.25rem);font-weight:400;color:#f0ece4;line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Landlord Insurance When Selling a Tenanted Brisbane Property: How to Maintain Cover Through to Settlement
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Selling a rental property does not end the seller's exposure to risk. Until settlement, the property is still the seller's, the tenancy may still be live, and any uninsured loss between contract and settlement is the seller's problem to absorb. Landlord cover stays relevant right up to handover.
      </p>
